organization.description: HuNI - Humanities Networked Infrastructure (http://huni.net.au) - is the Australian Virtual Laboratory for the Humanities, funded by the National eResearch Collaboration Tools and Resources (NeCTAR) project. It brings together data from 32 cultural heritage datasets into a graph database environment powered by Neo4j. Researchers and other users can explore the connections between people, places, organisations, concepts, events and works - and can add relationships between them, as well as building their own virtual collections. HuNI is managed by Deakin University on behalf of a consortium of 13 Australian institutions.
organization.title: HuNI - Humanities Networked Infrastructure

name: huni-persons
notes: HuNI (Humanities Networked Infrastructure) combines data from many Australian cultural websites into the biggest humanities and creative arts database ever assembled in Australia: http://huni.net.au  HuNI data covers all disciplines and brings together information about the people, works, events, organisations and places that make up the country's rich cultural landscape. This dataset contains HuNI's "Persons" data, consisting of 320,178 triples.
